nodes.description:
This is a very nice standing desk. The base is fully adjustable from 30 in to 50 in, so it's a sitting desk when you want one too. It's good to move around during the day.

The top is 24 x 48 in solid Spalted Maple with a "river" of color-shift epoxy. I use select slabs that are either reclaimed or sustainably grown with plenty of character from trusted sources.

The legs are Vivo brand so super solid construction. The electric motor is smooth and can be adjusted to fractions of an inch. More than one person using the standing desk? No problem: It comes with three memory settings.

I'm happy to ship you the base at cost from Amazon. Or you can buy your own. 24 x 48 in is a standard size.
nodes.title: Spalted maple and color-shift epoxy standing desk

nodes.description:
This is a gorgeous black walnut and epoxy desk. It's silky smooth to the touch. You can attach a standing desk base. I use a Vivo base that goes from 30 in all the way to 50 in. So it's a sitting desk too if you want it.

I can ship you the standing desk base at cost. Or you can buy your own.
nodes.title: Walnut and epoxy desktop

nodes.description:
This one-of-a-kind long narrow coffee table is live-edge walnut with black epoxy on black hairpin legs. The legs are attached with threaded inserts.

You can choose walnut for this classic look or maple for something a little brighter. Choose from any of the available colors for the "river" of epoxy.
nodes.title: Walnut and epoxy coffee table

nodes.description:
Inspired by the deep purple color of the epoxy, how could I not call this Black Walnut and epoxy charcuterie the Hard Rock? 

I went through a short period of self-doubt that I could continue to pull off naming designs after music genres, but I found a good website with them all on so I have renewed optimism.

The color's subtle. It's jet black epoxy, which is always a safe bet. But with a smidge, a whiff, a soup√ßon of violet & purple mica powder. You really don't need much to make a difference.

This is perfectly food safe because I use Odie's Oil exclusively. This is a fabulous way to present delicate cold cuts and slices of delicious cheese. It is not a cutting board or a trivet: Sharp knives and hot dishes will spoil the look. Full care instructions included with each board.
nodes.title: The Hard Rock Charcuterie Board

nodes.description:
Yet another take on the usual Black Walnut and epoxy charcuterie boards. This one's in the very popular 10 in x 18 in size.

If nothing else I'm learning some really good words for semi-transparent. I like diaphanous and gossamer. But how could I miss pellucid! I'm going to claim it was totally intentional.

Like all my boards, it's finished in Odie's Oil, which is completely food safe. And like all of them too: No sharp knives or hot dishes.

Enjoy!
nodes.title: The Ambient Charcuterie Board

nodes.description:
The is not your usual Black Walnut charcuterie board. It's the same epoxy as always but with floating flakes of fake gold. It's locked solid in epoxy so I could claim it's real gold. But it's not. 

The see-through "river" makes this item truly unique.
nodes.title: The Jazz Charcuterie Board

nodes.description:
Spalted Maple is a great backdrop for this classic blue river. This is how river tables got their start.

It doesn't have to be blue: Pick any color you can imagine and I'll make one for you. There are lots of good options for vivid colors on this lighter wood.

It's a charcuterie board. It's not a cutting board or a trivet. Each board is finished with Odie's Oil and is completely food safe.
nodes.title: The Blues Charcuterie Board

nodes.description:
The Classical is just that: Black Walnut and black epoxy. 

Each board measures 12 in x 16 in x 3/4 in and has four non-slip silicone feet.

We start with unfinished slabs so each is unique. 

Boards are finished with Odie's Oil, which is completely food safe. 

Will not hold up to significant chopping and definitely no hot dishes. But looks stunning as a charcuterie board and will definitely be a talking point.
nodes.title: The Classical Charcuterie Board

nodes.description:
A different take on a classic design. 

This one is Black Walnut but with copper mica flakes in the epoxy. The wood had a natural split in the middle, so I incorporated it as a second river. More of a tributary really.

You don't have to have copper: Pick any color you can imagine and I'll make one for you! But this is a pretty combination, don't you think?

It's a charcuterie board. It's not a cutting board or a trivet. Each board is finished with Odie's Oil and is completely food safe.
nodes.title: The Baroque Charcuterie Board
